      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Heat the oil in a large saucepan",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add onion, leek and ginger and chook over a medium heat for 10 mins until they are soft.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Stir in the celeria, apples & thyme and cook for a few more minutes.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Pour in the stock and some seasoning and simmer for 30 more minutes or until celeriac is tender.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "When the celeriac is tender, remove the soup from the heat and use a hand blender or food processor to blitz it until it is smooth.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Stir in ½ the creme fraiche.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Optional - Cut the bacon into roughly 1cm pieces and fry until crispy.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Serve, dolloping the remainder of the creme fraiche into each bowl. Scatter bacon on top.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Add salt a pinch at a time, tasting. If still flat, finish with a squeeze of lemon or a splash of vinegar to lift it.",
              "cause": "Underseasoned, or the aromatics weren't sweated long enough.",
              "symptom": "The soup tastes flat"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Stir cream in off the heat, or use crème fraîche, which doesn't split. Don't reboil after adding.",
              "cause": "Dairy added at too high a heat, or left to simmer after.",
              "symptom": "Cream-based soup splits"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Loosen with hot stock or water, a ladle at a time, until it pours from the spoon in a ribbon.",
              "cause": "Reduced too far, or the starch in the veg sets up on cooling.",
              "symptom": "Blended soup is too thick"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Simmer uncovered to reduce, or blitz in another roasted veg (potato, parsnip) to thicken.",
              "cause": "Stock-to-veg ratio too high.",
              "symptom": "Blended soup is too thin"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Vegan version: swap dairy cream for cashew cream (soak 100 g cashews in hot water, blend smooth) or oat cream.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Smokier finish: stir in a teaspoon of smoked paprika at the end, or top with crispy chorizo.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make a day ahead; the flavour deepens overnight in the fridge.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about, the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
